[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":196},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2019\u002F07\u002F17\u002Fhexo-seo-404-page\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2019\u002F07\u002F17\u002Fhexo-seo-404-page\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2019\u002F07\u002F17\u002Fhexo-seo-404-page\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2019\u002F07\u002F17\u002Fhexo-seo-404-page\u002F":172,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2019\u002F07\u002F17\u002Fhexo-seo-404-page\u002F":181},"\u002Fhexo\u002F20190717\u002F3365093327\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":156,"date":157,"description":19,"extension":158,"lang":159,"meta":160,"navigation":161,"path":162,"readingMinutes":163,"seo":164,"standalone":165,"stem":166,"tags":167,"tldr":169,"updated":157,"url":170,"__hash__":171},"content\u002Fen\u002FHexo\u002Fhexo-seo-404-page.md","Hexo SEO Detail: The 404 Page Matters","7233905633",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":147},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,29,39,43,48,52,55,62,65,69,72,80,92,97,100,140,143],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Pulling out one SEO detail into its own post — the 404 page.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"environment-for-this-post","Environment for this post",[25,26,28],"h3",{"id":27},"hexo-version","Hexo version",[30,31,32,36],"ul",{},[33,34,35],"li",{},"hexo: 3.8.0",[33,37,38],{},"hexo-cli: 2.0.0",[25,40,42],{"id":41},"next-version","NexT version",[30,44,45],{},[33,46,47],{},"NexT: 7.1.0",[12,49,51],{"id":50},"the-404-page","The 404 page",[17,53,54],{},"Sometimes tech blogs change URLs a lot after a not-so-great initial setup. But by then, search engine crawlers have already indexed your blog. On GitHub, broken links land on the default 404 page:",[17,56,57],{},[58,59],"img",{"alt":60,"src":61},"Default 404","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F1PjvKrD.png",[17,63,64],{},"Why call out the 404 page specifically? GitHub's default isn't terrible per se, but there's a problem: when a user or crawler lands on a non-existent page, there's no way to navigate back to your home page. That's a bad experience for users, and even worse for crawlers — which hurts your SEO rankings.",[12,66,68],{"id":67},"building-a-404-page","Building a 404 page",[17,70,71],{},"The fix is to build your own 404 page (or grab a free one online). Two things to include:",[30,73,74,77],{},[33,75,76],{},"Auto-redirect back to the home page after a short delay",[33,78,79],{},"A clearly visible button to go home",[17,81,82,83,87,88,91],{},"Where should the 404 page live? In my case I put it under ",[84,85,86],"code",{},"theme\u002Fsource",", and the filename has to be ",[84,89,90],{},"404.html",".",[17,93,94],{},[58,95],{"alt":90,"src":96},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F2YRXDdf.png",[17,98,99],{},"The HTML file also needs this at the very top, or Hexo won't recognise it:",[101,102,107],"pre",{"className":103,"code":104,"language":105,"meta":106,"style":106},"language-hexo shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","---\nlayout: false\ncomments: false\ntitle: 404 - Funny meeting you here!\n---\n","hexo","",[84,108,109,117,123,129,135],{"__ignoreMap":106},[110,111,114],"span",{"class":112,"line":113},"line",1,[110,115,116],{},"---\n",[110,118,120],{"class":112,"line":119},2,[110,121,122],{},"layout: false\n",[110,124,126],{"class":112,"line":125},3,[110,127,128],{},"comments: false\n",[110,130,132],{"class":112,"line":131},4,[110,133,134],{},"title: 404 - Funny meeting you here!\n",[110,136,138],{"class":112,"line":137},5,[110,139,116],{},[17,141,142],{},"Below that, it's your own HTML, images, and so on.",[144,145,146],"style",{},"html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: 